  "title": "PMO – Core Banking Transformation",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>- Support planning and execution of transformation activities across multiple workstreams</p><p>- Develop and maintain project plans, dashboards, milestone trackers, and reports</p><p>- Track and report progress, risks, issues, and dependencies</p><p>- Facilitate stakeholder meetings, workshops, and steering committees</p><p>- Ensure documentation of scope, requirements, decisions, and governance artifacts</p><p>- Coordinate with business analysts, architects, vendors, and delivery teams</p><p>- Support resource planning, budgeting, and financial tracking</p><p>- Maintain alignment with regulatory, compliance, and audit requirements</p><p>- Support change management and communication activities</p><p>- Drive executive-level reporting<br /><br /><strong>Required Skills & Experience:</strong><br /><br />Bachelor’s degree in Business, IT, or related field</p><p>- 2+ years of experience</p><p>- Experience in project management or PMO roles within banking or financial services</p><p>- Strong understanding of Agile, Waterfall, or Hybrid methodologies</p><p>- Proficiency in MS Project, JIRA, Confluence, Excel, and PowerPoint</p><p>- Experience in large-scale transformation programs preferred</p><p>- Strong communication and stakeholder management skills</p>",
